Dream Cafe Pattern in Sales and Frequent Menu Item Exploration
--------------------------------------------------------------

CafÃ© culture is becoming more popular, coffee and a slice of cake can be the center attraction whether it’s self-introspection: writing ion your journal, studying for an exam, or having a quick break from work. Dream cafe, a popular local coffee shop located in BGC is located near offices, condominiums and schools. This cafe is known for their arabica beans and their unique food combinations. With a capacity of 50 persons, and business hours from 7 AM - 11 PM, and its location is perfect for customers and stay to relax, study, or have a meeting and chat.

In this paper, in order to find frequent pattern in sales and frequent menu item combinations, we answers these questions and divide the process in these steps

1.  Data Cleaning
2.  Which combinations of items sell more frequently compared to. #Eclat
3.  Which food-item do most people tend to buy with their drink #rhs stuff
4.  When do people tend to buy an item #item frequency plot
5.  Explore if important association rules or item sets vary over time (within a day) #visualisation

### Data Cleaning

1.  Create a promo tag - if transaction is done within promo period
2.  Create a d rink tag and separate size - for easier association rules
3.  Create a time of day tag (breakfast, brunch, lunch, snack, dinner, late night)
4.  Transform data set into transaction data and partition by time of day.

In this part, we remove transactions that were done during the promo period as not to contaminate the dataset.

### Which Combination of Items Sell More Frequently than Others?

We divide the analysis into 7 parts, first part is we identify the combinations of items that sells more frequently compared to others using the whole day transactions and do the same analysis for the time period

#### All Day

During the whole day, we can see that the combination of Dayap Cheesecake and Vanilla Caffe Frappe, Iced Caramel Macchiato and Vanilla Caffe Frappe, and Vanilla Caffe Frappe and White Chocolate Mocha Frappe led to most sells.

### When do people tend to buy an item

People tend to buy an item during 11 am- 1 pm, 3 PM - 5 PM . and 7 PM - 9 PM which can be considered lunch, snack time, and dinner and Vanilla Caffe Frappe is a best seller for all the time period.

### Suggest at least 5 association rules

For the association rules, we also divide the analysis as overall, breakfast, brunch, lunch, snack, dinner, and late snack in order to catch the differences that vary over time.

### All

Looking at the overall transaction data, we can see that the most popular transaction is Banoffee Pie,Classic Sausage Roll,Iced Caffe Latte,Iced Caramel Macchiato and Vanilla Caffe Frappe. Another popular transactions is Banoffee Pie,Classic Sausage Roll,Iced Caffe Latte,Iced Caramel Macchiato and Dayap Cheesecake. If someone bought Dayap Cheesecake , s/he is likely to have bought Iced Caffe Latte as well.

generating rules
================

association.rules <- apriori(tr, parameter = list(supp=0.001, conf=0.75,maxlen=10)) inspect(association.rules)

visualization
=============

subRules<-association.rules\[quality(association.rules)$confidence>0.75\] top10subRules <- head(subRules, n = 5, by = “confidence”) plot(top10subRules, method = “graph”, engine = “htmlwidget”)

which item causes the other items
=================================

subRules2<-head(subRules, n=20, by=“lift”) plot(subRules2, method=“paracoord”)

#### Breakfast

Looking at the overall breakfast transaction data, we can see that the most popular transaction is the combination of Iced Caffe Latte,White Chocolate Mocha Frappe, and Classic Chocolate Cake. If someone bought Dayap Cheesecake , s/he is likely to have bought Blueberry Muffin as well. People who buy. People who buy bought Dayap Cheesecake is likely to have bought Chicken Pastel Pie as well. Mostly are pastries, caskes, and food items that is mostly eaten for breakfast.
